Almarai, Saudi Vitrified, Herfy Food: Saudi Equity Preview

-- B y   M o u r a d   H a r o u t u n i a n
-- 
2011-09-03T06:33:12Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-03/almarai-saudi-vitrified-herfy-food-saudi-equity-preview.html
The following stocks may rise or
fall in  Saudi Arabia ’s market. Stock symbols are in parentheses
and prices are from the last close.  The  Tadawul All Share Index (SASEIDX)  gained 1 percent to 5,979.30 on
Aug. 24.  Almarai Co. (ALMARAI AB): Saudi Arabia’ largest food
producer by market value appointed Georges Schorderet as chief
operating officer. Paul Gay succeeded Schorderet as chief
financial officer and Malcolm Jordan was named general manager
of marketing. The shares were unchanged at 86 riyals.  Herfy Food Services Co. (HERFY)  : The Saudi Arabian fast-
food chain obtained a loan valued at 45 million riyals ($12
million) from the Saudi Industrial Development Fund to finance a
plant under construction in the Second Industrial City in
Riyadh. The shares dropped 0.7 percent to 77 riyals.  Saudi Vitrified Clay Pipe Co. (SVCP AB): The manufacturer
of clay pipes and fittings signed a memorandum of understanding
to acquire Arabian Company for Water Pipe Industry, known as
Acwa Pipe. Saudi Vitrified will raise its capital by issuing
stock for Acwa Pipe. Saudi Vitrified’s shares rose 0.9 percent
to 55.75 riyals.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Mourad Haroutunian in  Riyadh  at 
